with signs of burning or melting of wiring

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turbocharger header pipe can cause a loss of power, decreased engine performance, and potentially lead to engine damage or failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: loud noises or rattling sounds from the engine
visible signs of cracks or damage to the turbocharger header pipe.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake squeal and premature wear can lead to reduced braking performance, increasing the stopping distance and risk of accidents. In severe cases, the caliper falling out can cause the vehicle to pull to one side, further compromising safety.
symptoms: Squealing or grinding noise when applying the brakes
premature wear on brake pads and rotors
vehicle pulls to one side while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Sealing of Doors and Body
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the doors and body to properly seal can allow dirt and dust to enter the vehicle, causing difficulty for passengers to see and breathe, which can lead to discomfort, health issues, and potentially even accidents.
symptoms: Dirt and dust entering the vehicle through the front and back doors

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracking or failure of the rear suspension can lead to a loss of vehicle control, reduced stability, and increased risk of accidents, especially at high speeds or during sudden maneuvers.
symptoms: Unusual noises or creaking sounds from the rear suspension
difficulty steering or maintaining directional control.
